==English==

===Etymology===
From [[fruit]] + [[-ful]]

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Favourable to the growth of [[fruit]] or useful [[vegetation]]; [[fertile]]; not [[barren]].
# Being [[productive]] in any sense; yielding [[benefit]]s.
#: ''The extra work in the office turned out to be '''fruitful''' after all - I got promoted''

====Quotations====
*{{RQ:Authorized Version}} Genesis, I, 22
*: And God blessed them, saying, Be '''fruitful''', and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas, and let fowl multiply in the earth.

====Related terms====
*[[fruitfully]]
*[[fruitfulness]]

